By Sampson Unamka  UK-based gospel singer, Seyi Weli, has said she wanted her songs to not only appeal to people globally but to also showcase Nigerian culture and heritage. Currently in the country, the singer will be promoting her debut single, Agidigba and Victory, which is scheduled to drop in April, 2020. According to her, Agidigba is an afrobeats gospel song which reflects on the greatness and goodness of God. The song is also a re-commitment to God, adding that the video was shot in London with direction coming from Uvi Orogun who has shot music videos for Nathaniel Bassey and Sonnie Badu. Regarding her music and her return home, the chartered engineer and mother of two said: “I want to bring music that showcases our culture and heritage.  And also one that appeals to my fellow Nigerians and not only Nigerians but to also people all over the world. It’s good that we don’t shy away from our heritage and our culture, show your culture, and show your heritage, it might be what people want to embrace; something different.” Seyi Weli who is from a musical family, sang in choirs from elementary school through to university. She was an active choir member and worship leader for over a decade at RCCG Scotland Headquarters church – Fountain of Love. She supported fellow members as a backup vocalist for their albums and was a member of Sound of Many Waters, an interdenominational and multicultural gospel band in Scotland, UK.